        <updateDate>2011-09-02T21:39:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Veterans Day Moment of Silence Act - Directs the President to issue an annual proclamation calling on the people of the United States to observe two minutes of silence on Veterans Day, beginning at 2:11 p.m. eastern time, in honor of the service and sacrifice of veterans throughout the history of the nation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
